[{"id":40772,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Vernier constant is defined as the difference between the value of one main scale division and one vernier scale division. It is also known as the least count of vernier calliper.</p><p>The main scale division of the given vernier calliper is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>D</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></mrow><mn>20</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math>.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi><mi>C</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>M</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>D</mi></mrow><mi>n</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></mrow><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>05</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jun Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40774,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>00</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"L.C. of screw Gauge<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow><mn>50</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math><br />Zero error of screw Gauge <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>.</mo></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>05</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math><br />Reading of screw gauge <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo></math> main scale reading <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>+</mo></math> circular scale reading <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#215;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>.</mo><mo>-</mo></math>Zero error <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>20</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>05</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Aug Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40779,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>64</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>82</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>90</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>80</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Least count <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></mrow><mn>100</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math></p><p>zero error <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>LC</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>08</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math></p><p>True reading (Diameter)</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>72</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>LC</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo></math> (Zero error)</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>72</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>08</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>72</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>08</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>64</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math></p><p>therefore, radius <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>64</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>82</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi><mo>.</mo></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40759,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["Radius of curvature of concave surface","Specific rotation of liquids","Thickness of thin plates","Radius of curvature of convex surface"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>A spherometer is a device used for measuring the curvature of surfaces, particularly the radius of curvature of spherical or cylindrical surfaces. It consists of a central leg with a fine screw, and three outer legs that form a tripod. The device is primarily designed for measuring dimensions related to curved surfaces.</p><p>Specific rotation is a property related to the rotation of plane-polarized light in a substance. It is not measured using a spherometer. Instead, a polarimeter is typically used to measure specific rotation.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (27 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40750,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["$3.35 \\mathrm{~mm}$","$4.65 \\mathrm{~mm}$","$4.55 \\mathrm{~mm}$","$4.60 \\mathrm{~mm}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} & \\text { Least count }=\\frac{1}{100} \\mathrm{~mm}=0.01 \\mathrm{~mm} \\\\ & \\text { zero error }=+0.05 \\mathrm{~mm} \\\\ & \\text { Reading }=4 \\times 1 \\mathrm{~mm}+60 \\times 0.01 \\mathrm{~mm}-0.05 \\mathrm{~mm} \\\\ & =4.55 \\mathrm{~mm}\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (08 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":40764,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>001</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>002</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>002</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>005</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<blockquote><p>One main scale division&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>MSD</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>20</mn></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p><p>One vernier scale division&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>VSD</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>24</mn><mn>25</mn></mfrac><mi>MSD</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>24</mn><mn>25</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>20</mn></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo></math> Least count <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>LC</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>MSD</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>VSD</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>20</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>24</mn><mn>25</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mi>cm</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>20</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>25</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>500</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>002</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>002</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (29 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40794,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["$0.0430 \\mathrm{~cm}$","$0.3150 \\mathrm{~cm}$","$0.4300 \\mathrm{~cm}$","$0.2150 \\mathrm{~cm}$"],"answer":3,"solution":"Least count\n$$\n=\\frac{\\text { Value of } 1 \\text { part on main scale }}{\\text { Number of parts on vernier scale }}\n$$\n$$\n=\\frac{0.25}{5 \\times 100} \\mathrm{~cm}=5 \\times 10^{-4} \\mathrm{~cm}\n$$\nReading $=4 \\times 0.05 \\mathrm{~cm}+30 \\times 5 \\times 10^{-4} \\mathrm{~cm}$ $=(0.2+0.0150) \\mathrm{cm}=0.2150 \\mathrm{~cm}$ (Thickness of wire)","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr Shift 1 Online)","image":null},{"id":40754,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["$0.5$","$2$","$5$","$1$"],"answer":1,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} & 20 \\mathrm{VSD}=19 \\mathrm{MSD} \\\\ & 1 \\mathrm{VSD}=\\frac{19}{20} \\mathrm{MSD} \\\\ & \\text { L.C. }=1 \\mathrm{MSD}-1 \\mathrm{VSD} \\\\ & 0.1 \\mathrm{~mm}=1 \\mathrm{MSD}-\\frac{19}{20} \\mathrm{MSD} \\\\ & 0.1=\\frac{1}{20} \\mathrm{MSD} \\\\ & 1 \\mathrm{MSD}=2 \\mathrm{~mm}\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (05 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":40787,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["<math><mn>4.0</mn><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>m</mi><mi>m</mi></math>","Zero","<math><mn>5.0</mn><mi> </mi><mi>m</mi><mi>m</mi></math>","<math><mn>3.0</mn><mi> </mi><mi>m</mi><mi>m</mi></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<math><mi>δ</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>ρ</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mi>v</mi><mi>g</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>L</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math><msup><mrow><mi>δ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>′</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>ρ</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi>ρ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>L</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced><mi>v</mi><mi>g</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>L</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>⇒</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>δ</mi><mo>^</mo><mi>′</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>δ</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>ρ</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi>ρ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>L</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>ρ</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>8</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>8</mn></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math><msup><mrow><mi>δ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>′</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>m</mi><mi>m</mi></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (12 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":40756,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>Time period of a simple pendulum is given by, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>π</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi><mi>g</mi></mfrac></mfenced></math>.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>g</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>π</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi></mrow><msup><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math></p><p>Therefore, fractional error will be</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>Δ</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow><mi>g</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>Δ</mi><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>Δ</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mi>T</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mn>20</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>40</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mn>20</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Percentage change <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mn>20</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>%</mo></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (31 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":40757,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mi>mm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn><mo> </mo><mi>mm</mi></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The number of divisions on the vernier scale <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>50</mn></math></p><p>Main scale division <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>MSD</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo> </mo><mi>mm</mi></math></p><p>As, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>50</mn></math> divisions on the vernier scale coincide with <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>49</mn></math> divisions on the main scale,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>VSD</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>49</mn><mn>50</mn></mfrac><mi>MSD</mi></math></p><p>The minimum inaccuracy in the measurement of distance by a vernier scale,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo></math> Least count of the vernier scale</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mi>MSD</mi><mo>–</mo><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mi>VSD</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mi>MSD</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mn>9</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>5</mn><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>MSD</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>5</mn><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>MSD</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>50</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>0</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">.</mi><mn>5</mn><mo> </mo><mi>mm</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn><mo> </mo><mi>mm</mi></math>.</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (30 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":40766,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Given,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>MSD</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>VSD</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>MSD</mi></math></p><p>Then,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>VSD</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mi>MSD</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>MSD</mi></math></p><p>Least count of Vernier calliper is L.C. <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p><p>Positive zero error<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>04</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p><p>Observed reading of diameter of spherical bob<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p><p>Real reading of diameter of bob<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>04</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>412</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (27 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40767,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>02</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>06</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Given that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math></p><p>And&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>9</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math></p><p>L.C of vernier caliper <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p><p>Zero error <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>10</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math>&nbsp;as&nbsp;at zero the, the zero of the vernier is shifted towards&nbsp;left zero error is negative. Therefore, zero error<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math>.</p><p>Reading <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><mo>-</mo></math> &nbsp;Zero error</p><p>Reading<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn><mo>-</mo><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>06</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>Reading<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>06</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>06</mn></math></p><p>Reading<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p><p>The closest option is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":40775,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> is not correct but <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math> is correct.","Both <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math> are correct and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math> is the correct explanation of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>.</mo></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> is correct but <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math> is not correct.","Both <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math> are correct and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math> is NOT the correct explanation of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>.</mo></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Least count <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mtext>&#160;Pitch&#160;</mtext><mtext>&#160;total division on circular scale&#160;</mtext></mfrac></math><br />In <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math> revolution, distance travel,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi><mo>.</mo></math></p><p>In <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math> revolution, it will travel <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi><mo>.</mo></math><br />So the least count <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>50</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>02</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (27 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40751,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["$2.0 \\mathrm{~g} / \\mathrm{cm}^3$","$1.7 \\mathrm{~g} / \\mathrm{cm}^3$","$2.2 \\mathrm{~g} / \\mathrm{cm}^3$","$2.5 \\mathrm{~g} / \\mathrm{cm}^3$"],"answer":0,"solution":"Given $9 \\mathrm{MSD}=10 \\mathrm{VSD}$\n$\\operatorname{mass}=8.635 \\mathrm{~g}$\n$\\begin{aligned} & \\mathrm{LC}=1 \\mathrm{MSD}-1 \\mathrm{VSD} \\\\ & \\mathrm{LC}=1 \\mathrm{MSD}-\\frac{9}{10} \\mathrm{MSD} \\\\ & \\mathrm{LC}=\\frac{1}{10} \\mathrm{MSD} \\\\ & \\mathrm{LC}=0.01 \\mathrm{~cm}\\end{aligned}$\nReading of diameter $=\\mathrm{MSR}+\\mathrm{LC} \\times \\mathrm{VSR}$\n$\\begin{aligned} & =2 \\mathrm{~cm}+(0.01) \\times(2) \\\\ & =2.02 \\mathrm{~cm}\\end{aligned}$\nVolume of sphere $=\\frac{4}{3} \\pi\\left(\\frac{d}{2}\\right)^3=\\frac{4}{3} \\pi\\left(\\frac{2.02}{2}\\right)^3$\n$=4.32 \\mathrm{~cm}^3$\nDensity $=\\frac{\\text { mass }}{\\text { volume }}=\\frac{8.635}{4.32}=1.998 \\sim 2.00 \\mathrm{~g}$<br />","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (08 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40781,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["Negative, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>&#956;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","Positive <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mi>&#956;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","Positive <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mi>m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","Positive, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>m</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"&nbsp;","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (06 Sep Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40753,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["21","142","71","42"],"answer":2,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} & \\mathrm{MSR}=1 \\mathrm{~mm}, \\mathrm{CSR}=42, \\text { pitch }=1 \\mathrm{~mm} \\\\ & \\mathrm{LC}=\\frac{\\text { pitch }}{\\text { No. of CSD }}=\\left(\\frac{1}{100}\\right)=0.01 \\mathrm{~mm} \\\\ & \\text { Diameter }=\\mathrm{MSR}+\\mathrm{LC} \\times \\mathrm{CSD} \\\\ & \\text { Diameter }=1+(0.01) \\times 42 \\mathrm{~mm} \\\\ & \\text { Diameter }=1.42 \\mathrm{~mm}=\\frac{\\mathrm{x}}{50} \\\\ & \\therefore \\mathrm{x}=71\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (06 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40777,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>36</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>54</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>58</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>56</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Positive zero error <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math></p><p>Main scale reading <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p><p>Vernier scale reading<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>01</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>06</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p><p>Final reading<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>06</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>02</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>54</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (17 Mar Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40796,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["<math><mn>0.70</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&nbsp;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math><mn>0.50</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&nbsp;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math><mn>0.75</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&nbsp;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math><mn>0.80</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&nbsp;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p><math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0.5</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>50</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0.01</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math><br /><br />Zero error <math><mo>=</mo><mn>0.50</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0.45</mn><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>0.05</mn></math><br /><br />Thickness <math><mo>=</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>0.5</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>0.01</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>0.05</mn></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0.50</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>0.25</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>0.05</mn></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0.80</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2016 (03 Apr)","image":null},{"id":40799,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["A meter scale","A vernier calliper where the 10 divisions in vernier scale matches with 9 division in main scale and main scale has 10 divisions in 1 cm","A screw gauge having 100 divisions in the circular scale and pitch as 1 mm","A screw gauge having 50 divisions in the circular scale and pitch as 1 mm"],"answer":1,"solution":"As per given data the Vernier has a least count of 0.01 cm, which is consistent with the information given in question.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2014 (06 Apr)","image":null},{"id":40761,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Least count of screw gauge is<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>Pitch</mi><mrow><mi>No</mi><mo>.</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>of</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>circular</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>divisions</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></mrow><mn>100</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Least count,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi><mi>C</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math></p><p>The zero of circular scale lies <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn></math>&nbsp;divisions below the line of graduation. So, zero error is positive.</p><p>Positive zero error&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>R</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>C</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>R</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>L</mi><mi>C</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>Diameter of wire,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>R</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>C</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>R</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>L</mi><mi>C</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>&#8211;</mo><mi>Positive</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>zero</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>error</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>46</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>40</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math></p><p>Hence, diameter of wire is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>220</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (30 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40780,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>.5375</mo><mo>&#177;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.0739</mo></mrow></mfenced><mi>mm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>.5375</mo><mo>&#177;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.0740</mo></mrow></mfenced><mi>mm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>.538</mo><mo>&#177;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.074</mo></mrow></mfenced><mi>mm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>.54</mo><mo>&#177;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.07</mo></mrow></mfenced><mi>mm</mi></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Significant rule says that reading should has same significant figure as that of reading given.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5375</mn><mo>&#8594;</mo></math> rounded to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8594;</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>54</mn><mo>.</mo></math></p><p>0.07395<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8594;</mo></math>&nbsp;rounded to<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8594;</mo></math>0.07</p><p>therefore,&nbsp;<sub><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>54</mn><mo>&#177;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>07</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>m</mi></math></sub></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (06 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":40785,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["<math><mn>384</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math><mn>332</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math><mn>338</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math><mn>379</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"Speed of sound, <math><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>f</mi><mtext> </mtext><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>l</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi>l</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced></math>  <br/><math><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>480</mn><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>0.70</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0.30</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>  <br/><math><mo>=</mo><mn>384</mn><mtext> </mtext><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></mrow><mo>/</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></mrow></mrow></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (12 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":40743,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["$1.50$","$1.48$","$1.54$","$1.51$"],"answer":2,"solution":"For a screw gauge, the measurement formula is: Reading = Pitch scale + (Circular scale × Least count) - Zero error<br>The zero of circular scale lies 3 divisions above the pitch line, indicating negative zero error:<br>Zero error = -3 × 0.01 = -0.03 mm<br>Reading = 1 + (51 × 0.01) - (-0.03) = 1 + 0.51 + 0.03 = 1.54 mm","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (23 January Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40804,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["one minute","half minute","one degree","half degree"],"answer":0,"solution":"$$\n\\text { Least count }=\\frac{\\text { value of main scale division }}{\\text { No of divisions on vernier scale }}=\\frac{1}{30} \\mathrm{MSD}=\\frac{1}{30} \\times \\frac{1}{2}^{\\circ}=\\frac{1}{60}^{\\circ}=1 \\text { minute }\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2009","image":null},{"id":40793,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["<math><mn>5.755</mn><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>m</mi><mi>m</mi></math>","<math><mn>5.740</mn><mi> </mi><mi>m</mi><mi>m</mi></math>","<math><mn>5.725</mn><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>m</mi><mi>m</mi></math>","<math><mn>5.950</mn><mi> </mi><mi>m</mi><mi>m</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<blockquote><p>least count <math><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0.5</mn><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>m</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>100</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0.005</mn><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>m</mi><mi>m</mi></math><br /><br />Reading <math><mo>=</mo><mn>5.5</mn><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>m</mi><mi>m</mi><mo>+</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mn>48</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>0.005</mn><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>m</mi><mi>m</mi></math><br /><br /><math><mo>=</mo><mn>5.725</mn><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>m</mi><mi>m</mi><mo>.</mo></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":40806,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["$3.32 \\mathrm{~mm}$","$3.73 \\mathrm{~mm}$","$3.67 \\mathrm{~mm}$","$3.38 \\mathrm{~mm}$"],"answer":3,"solution":"Diameter $=$ M.S.R. $+$ C.S.R $\\times$ L.C. $+$ Z.E. $=3+35 \\times(0.5 / 50)+0.03=3.38 \\mathrm{~mm}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2008","image":null},{"id":40773,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>9</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>D</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>V</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>D</mi></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>V</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>D</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>D</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>L</mi><mo>.</mo><mi>C</mi><mo>.</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>M</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>V</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>D</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>M</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>D</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow><mn>1</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></math><br />Reading <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo></math> Main scale reading <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>+</mo></math> L.C. <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#215;</mo></math> vernier scale reading<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></mfenced></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math></p><p>Reading of diameter<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math><br />radius of the bob<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>52</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>52</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (31 Aug Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":40788,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["<math><mn>50</mn></math>","<math><mn>100</mn></math>","<math><mn>500</mn></math>","<math><mn>200</mn></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Least count of screw gauge <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mi>&#956;m</mi></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mo>.</mo><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">f</mi><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">v</mi><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">u</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi><mtext>&#8201;&#8201;</mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#956;m</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math><mi>N</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>200</mn></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (12 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":40792,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Experimental Physics","question":"","options":["<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>12</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>L</mi></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>11</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>24</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>L</mi></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>11</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>12</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>L</mi></math>","<math><mfrac><mrow><mn>13</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>24</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi>L</mi></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"Potential difference across <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AJ</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>I</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>R</mi><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>J</mi></mrow></msub></math>,<br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>&#949;</mi><mrow><mn>13</mn><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#183;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>12</mn><mi>r</mi></mrow><mi>L</mi></mfrac><mo>&#183;</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></math><br /><br />For no current in galvanometer,<br /><br /><math><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#949;</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo></math> potential difference across <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AJ</mi></math><br /><br /><math><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#949;</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>12</mn><mi>&#949;</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>13</mn><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfrac><mi>x</mi></math><br /><br /><math><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>13L</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>24</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (10 Jan Shift 1)","image":null}]